PROJECT: Israeli Coffee Cart Review Platform
STACK: Next.js 15, TypeScript, Tailwind, MySQL

ARCHITECTURE DECISIONS:

- App Router (not Pages Router)
- Server Components by default, Client Components only when needed
- Separate /components/ui for reusable components

CODE STYLE:

- TypeScript strict mode always
- Functional components only
- Use shadcn/ui for base components
- Hebrew RTL support from day one
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Commit concise messages after completing todos in a task

API & DATA:

- Server Actions for mutations
- Zod for validation

NAMING CONVENTIONS:

- Files and folders: kebab-case
- Components: PascalCase
- Function and variables: camelCase
- Constants: SCREAMING_CASE
- Database tables: snake_case (coffee_carts, user_reviews)

FEATURES TO BUILD FIRST:

1. Cart listing and search
2. User auth
3. Rating/review system
4. Map integration
5. Image upload

DON'T:

- Don't use client components unless interactive
- Don't skip TypeScript types
- Don't hardcode - use env variables
- Don't add line comments unless really necessary
